ial workers, with specific reference to effective assessments.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","137142","2018-04-26T15:17:19.683Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890093/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890093/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-23","Carers: Mental Capacity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the criteria are for capacity tests used to assess a person's suitability to look after a child; and what guidance his Department has issued on the use of those criteria.","false","Biography information for Darren Jones","Bristol North West","Darren Jones","137143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890094","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-26","<p>The Secretary of State regularly meets a wide range of stakeholders to discuss a number of issues.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-04-26T11:22:26.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890094/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890094/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-23","Department of Health and Social Care: Local Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many meetings he has had with representatives of local authorities since 1 January 2018.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","137144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890095","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-26","<p>The number of defendants proceeded against at magistrates’ courts for drugs offences, in the Cheshire Police Force area, from 2010 to 2016, can be viewed in the table. All prosecutions, including those for indictable drugs offences, commence in a magistrates’ court.</p><p> </p><p>Court proceedings data for 2017 are planned for publication in May 2018.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Defendants proceeded against at magistrates courts for drugs offences, Cheshire Police Force Area, 2010 to 2016 <sup>(1)(2)</sup></strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Force/Local Justice Area</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cheshire</p></td><td><p>857</p></td><td><p>836</p></td><td><p>886</p></td><td><p>888</p></td><td><p>997</p></td><td><p>1,014</p></td><td><p>949</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>of which:</em></p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Halton <sup>(3)</sup></p></td><td><p>119</p></td><td><p>161</p></td><td><p>278</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North Cheshire <sup>(3)</sup></p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>358</p></td><td><p>421</p></td><td><p>372</p></td><td><p>424</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>'-' Nil</p><p>(1) The figures given in the table relate to persons for whom these offences were the principal offences for which they were dealt with. When a defendant has been found guilty of two or more offences it is the offence for which the heaviest penalty is imposed. Where the same disposal is imposed for two or more