"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887888","Wales Office","false","2018-04-26","<p>We are discussing the publication of this material with the Welsh Government and I will write to you when those discussions conclude.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2018-04-26T14:45:00.213Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887888/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887888/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-04-20","Severn River Crossing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, if he will publish the representations he has received from the Welsh Government on the renaming of the Second Severn Crossing.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","136883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887889","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-25","<p>At any time whilst payment is suspended as a result of a challenge to the tribunal judgement by the Secretary of State, a claimant can request that it is lifted on hardship grounds. Each case is considered on its merits and challenge will only be brought if we believe that a tribunal’s decision is erroneous in law.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-04-25T16:04:43.203Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887889/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887889/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-20","Personal Independence Payment: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what financial safeguards his Department have put in place to protect vulnerable claimants in the event that their claim is delayed as a result appeals by her Department on the First-tier decision to award personal Independence payments.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","136884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887890","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-25","<p>We will be publishing a Digital Railway Strategy with Network Rail and a public announcement on this strategy will be made shortly.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-04-25T11:32:53.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887890/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887890/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887890/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-20","Railways: Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to publish a digital railway (a) strategy and (b) delivery plan.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","136885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887891","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-26","<p>The Department will only seek to refer decisions of the First-tier Tribunal to the Upper Tribunal, in Personal Independence Payment cases as well as those of other benefits, where we contend that the First-tier Tribunal has made an error in law. Each case is considered on its merits.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-04-26T13:48:30.153Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887891/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887891/answer","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887891/answer/previousversion/54108","Biography information for Sarah Newton","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-20","Personal Independence Payment: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what criteria her Department uses for appealing decisions by the first-tier tribunal  to award personal independence payments.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","136886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887892","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-25","<p>Network Rail remains committed to completing the electrification of the Bolton to Preston line by December 2018. As part of overall assurance, the Government regularly reviews Network Rail’s projects.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-04-25T11:30:32.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887892/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887892/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887892/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-20","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what  the timetable is for the electrification of the Bolton to Preston line; and what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of Network Rail deliver the project.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","136887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887893","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-25","<p>There are no plans to amend the Franchise Agreements as there are existing provisions within the current agreements that deal with delays to planned timetable changes resulting from variations to infrastructure assumptions made at the time of the franchise bidding process.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-04-25T11:27:36.99Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887893/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887893/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887893/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-20","Railways: Timetables","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has plans to amend the (a) Northern, (b) Transpennine Express and (c) East Midlands Trains franchise as a result of the delay to the introduction of the May 2018 timetable.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","136888"
