"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887895","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-25","<p>Following the challenges of the May 2018 timetable production, Network Rail has formulated a plan in relation to delivering an efficient and effective timetabling process and provide timely information for passengers. The ORR, as independent regulator, will be assessing the robustness of this plan through to the December 2018 Timetable production, which I will be monitoring the progress of as the process continues.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-04-25T11:35:06.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887895/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887895/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-20","Railways: Timetables","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the capacity of Network Rail to (a) plan for and (b) deliver the December 2018 timetable.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","136890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887896","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-25","<p>The information requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Although diagnosis is recorded in the Mental Health Services Data Set, this is a new area of investigation on which detailed data quality assessment and detailed analysis would be required.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-04-25T11:12:41.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887896/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887896/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-20","Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people with dementia are currently detained under the Mental Health Act 1983.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","136891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887897","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-27","<p>The Government has not provided any financial support for research into the use, composting and recycling of polylactic acid for the manufacture of plastic bottles.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-04-27T13:24:49.3Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887897/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887897/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-20","Bottles: Plastics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what financial support the Government has provided for research into the use, composting and tertiary recycling of polylactic acid as fresh feedstock for the manufacture of plastic bottles in the last financial year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","136892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887898","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-27","<p>The Government has not had any discussions with industry representatives on setting a date by which polyethylene terephthalate in plastic bottles will be phased out and replaced by polylactic acid.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-04-27T13:21:47.22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887898/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887898/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-20","Bottles: Plastics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions he has had with industry representatives on setting a date by which polyethylene terephthalate in plastic bottles will have been phased out and replaced by polylactic acid.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","136893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887899","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-04-25","<p>Defra and the Animal and Plant Health Agency (APHA) monitor outbreaks of diseases in the UK and across the world and regularly publish our risk assessments on GOV.UK.</p><p>In August 2017, Defra’s risk assessment level was raised to low from very low in response to the spread of infection in Eastern Europe, and this has been widely communicated to the industry and pig keepers.</p><p>EU safeguard measures restrict the movement of pigs and pig products out of African swine fever (ASF) affected areas, and we receive regular updates on the application of disease control measures in each Member State. We are in regular dialogue with European colleagues to monitor the situation within the frameworks provided by the EU reference labs for ASF. The restriction zones cover a wide area.</p><p>Within the UK, further precautions to reduce the risk of accidental introduction or spread of disease include a ban on the feeding of swill and catering waste to animals and a standstill on movement after the introduction of new stock to a farm.</p><p>The movement of vehicles and people, particularly farm workers, and personal imports of pork products from ASF affected areas present a potential risk. Defra, APHA and the pig industry are working together on a communications campaign for pig keepers to highlight the increased risk of ASF. This has focused on the importance of biosecurity and on raising awareness of the disease risks associated with the illegal feeding of kitchen waste or pork products to pigs.</p><p>Tests for ASF are established, contingency plans are in place, and outbreak scenarios have been tested and will be further tested. If an outbreak of ASF occurred in the UK, Government policy would be to implement movement controls to prevent further spread of the disease, and to carry out a humane cull of pigs on affected premises in order to control and eradicate the disease and regain disease freedom.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-04-25T15:26:22.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887899/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887899/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-20","Swine Fever","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of trends in the level of incidences of swine fever in Europe; what recent assessment he has made of the level of risk of swine fever outbreaks in the UK; what contingency plans his Department has put in place in the event of an outbreak of swine fever in the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","136894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887900","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-27","<p>The Department is currently updating The Highway Code to reflect the changes made to legislation regarding learner drivers on motorways and on remote control parking.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-04-27T11:14:30.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887900/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887900/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-20","Highway Code","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to update the Highway Code.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","136895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887901","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-27","<p>Costs of individual systems on Dreadnought are managed within the programme's overall £31 billion budget, which is funded by Defence. I am withholding details of the cost of this system as disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice commercial discussions and interests.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","136897","2018-04-27T13:16:00.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887901/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887901/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-20","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent estimate his Department has made of the cost of the trim and compensation system for the Dreadnought programme; and whether that estimate is an increase on previously made estimates.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","136896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887902","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-27","<p>Costs of individual systems on Dreadnought are managed within the programme's overall £31 billion budget, which is funded by Defence. I am withholding details of the cost of this system as disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice commercial discussions and interests.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","136896","2018-04-27T13:16:00.863Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887902/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887902/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-20","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, from which budgets the cost of the Dreadnought programme’s trim and compensation system will be funded.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","136897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887903","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>​We regularly press both the Israelis and Palestinians to engage in direct negotiations that will lead to a safe and secure Israel living alongside a viable and sovereign Palestinian state. Most recently Lord Ahmad visited Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories (8-12 April) and stressed the need for an end to all actions that undermine the viability of the two-state solution with the Palestinian Authority Prime Minister Hamdallah, Israeli Minister of Regional Cooperation Tzachi Hanegbi and Israeli Minister of Justice Ayelet Shaked.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-04-30T16:05:54.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887903/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887903/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-20","Middle East: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his (a) Israeli and (b) Palestinian counterparts on the Middle East peace process.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","136898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887904","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-30","<p>I can confirm that the Ministry of Defence holds a copy of Exhibit 606, which is currently being retrieved from our archives. I will write to the hon. Member in due course with the relevant information.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-04-30T16:10:23.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887904/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887904/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-20","Tornado Aircraft: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of Exhibit 606 as listed in Part 2 of the Service Inquiry report into the accident involving Tornado GR4 ZD743 and Tornado GR4 ZD812 over the Moray Firth on 3 July 2012.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","136899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887905","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>The United Kingdom will always be grateful for the invaluable contribution made by the thousands of people who came to the UK from the Caribbean. The Government has therefore made considerable efforts to discuss immigration issues with Caribbean leaders and explain the urgent action being taken to rectify cases of those from the Windrush generation.</p><p>Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon, Minister of State for the Commonwealth and the Caribbean, and the Rt Hon Caroline Nokes MP, Minister of State for Immigration, met Commonwealth Caribbean Foreign Ministers on 16 April to discuss concerns about the immigration status of the Windrush generation. This was followed by a meeting between the Prime Minister and Caribbean leaders on 17 April. The Prime Minister also met the Prime Minister of Jamaica for a bilateral meeting. Lord Ahmad joined both discussions.</p><p>Lord Ahmad meets Caribbean High Commissioners quarterly and these issues will be discussed at the next scheduled meeting.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-04-30T14:27:16.21Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887905/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887905/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-20","Caribbean: Immigrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he intends to meet with representatives of the Caribbean to discuss concerns on the immigration status of people of Caribbean birth who have been living and working in the UK.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","136900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887906","Home Office","false","2018-07-02","<p>The numbers of individuals from Caribbean Commonwealth countries removed or deported from the United Kingdom since 2010 is published at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-year-ending-march-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-year-ending-march-2018 </a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-02T09:20:23.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887906/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887906/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-20","Immigrants: Caribbean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she has made an estimate of the number of citizens of Caribbean birth currently living in the UK who in each year since 2010 (a) have been told they do not have the right to remain in the UK, (b) are awaiting deportation and (c) have been deported.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","136901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/887907","Department for International Development","false","2018-04-26","<p>From 2010 to 2016, the UK has provided over £420m in bilateral Official Development Assistance (ODA) to Caribbean countries. In 2015, the DFID Caribbean programme increased by £330m, including through the establishment of the £300m UK Caribbean Infrastructure Fund (UKCIF).</p><p> </p><p>Following the devastation of Hurricanes Irma and Maria in 2017, the UK also provided over £185m in humanitarian and reconstruction support, mainly to the affected islands of Antigua and Barbuda, Dominica, British Virgin Islands, Turks and Caicos and Anguilla.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><em>figures in £ thousands</em></p></td><td><p><strong>£</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Antigua and Barbuda</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Barbados</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>52</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Belize</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>51</p></td><td><p>322</p></td><td><p>142</p></td><td><p>1,664</p></td><td><p>973</p></td><td><p>1,145</p></td><td><p>423</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dominica</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>195</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>34</p></td><td><p>32</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>492</p></td><td><p>44</p></td